{
  "stem": "18470.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 264.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because everything was kind of normal until then.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then one day in 1938, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] a storm trooper, an SA or SS man-- I don't remember exactly-- I think a guy was garbed in a yellow uniform.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that would have made him SA-- came into the room and said, after reading a protocol, all Jewish children are hereby expelled [NON-ENGLISH], and then he yelled, hier raus!",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So all the Jewish children consisted of Ruth Lichtenstein and myself.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Those were the only Jewish children in school at the time.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember with great humiliation, getting up and then the rest of the class chanting, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, from that point on, the word was out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You don't play with Jewish kids.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "However, within days after that event, I remember two nuns appeared at our doorstep in the evening one night, and invited my mother to send me to a Catholic school, which I did.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, I attended.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And to their credit, they-- they took considerable risk to do that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I used to come home at night, sitting down to dinner before saying the Motzi, the prayer over the bread, I crossed myself and then said the Motzi.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So never really seeing any contradiction in this, until my mother, years later, pointed it out to me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I still tell this to my Catholic friends with great joy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That you can-- you can have good people among the savagery that existed.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
